	{"heading":"Stardate 2405.1 (The Battle for Gamma)",
	"commentary":"<p>By stealing the initiative, it makes it much harder (or even impossible) for Elppa to defend their colonies. In short, we did a double on them to battle one of their colonies.</p><ol><li><b>Round 1</b>: Benefitting from fleet size bonus, our Flagship rolled a 10 (miss &gt;5)</li><li>Their Type II rolls a 7 against our scouts (miss &gt;4)</li><li>Our 8 Scouts rolled 1,3,4,4,6,6,7,8 (4 hits &le;4), utterly pulverizing their lone hull<br /><br /></li><li><b>Bombardment Round</b>: Our ships then rolled 3/2,2,2,7,7,7,8,9 (4 hits &le;3), easily reducing this colony to minimal strength. Our Transport then uses its equipment to finish off this colony.</li></ol><hr /><p>Since <i>their</i> primary fleet is still too close to our fleet, they never formed a secondary fleet. This is huge, as we are effectively using their limitations against them!</p>",
