	{"heading":"Stardate 2406.0 (Conclusion)",
	"commentary":"<p>Anti-climatic, but to be expected from a scenario that heavily emphasizes aggression. Relative to their homeworld, their planetary layout burned them. Even if they were smart enough to rally all hulls able to defend the homeworld (which would require overriding the scenario book), they would only have a mere <i>4</i> hulls, simply because we stole the initiative (denying the use of <b>11</b> more hulls)!</p><p>On top of that, we were able to expose a path before their sole fleet was able to make it very far from our own (distance &gt;4 hexes required for a fresh Replicator fleet). Finally, our Ancient Race gave us a near perfect start; we were able to collect 1 mineral marker short of the maximum possible.</p><p>As potent as Titans are, they are not right for every situation, especially on this Medium sized map. They also might not work out on higher difficulties, when we start with only the default quantity of colony ships; while the Replicators get RP pre-purchased, in addition to even more hulls. Anti-Replicator Transports are far easier to develop, but must be accompanied by other Hull Size 1 starships to discourage being sniped.</p>",
